Platinum,PT-10FB,,"10"" Flat Finishing Box",simple,"<h2>Achieve Flawless Drywall Finishes with Precision</h2><p>Elevate your drywall finishing workflow with the Platinum 10"" Flat Finishing Box. Engineered for contractors who demand consistency and speed, this tool streamlines the application of joint compound, allowing you to feather edges on both flat and butt joints in a single, fluid motion. By automating the distribution of compound, you can significantly reduce manual labor while ensuring a professional-grade finish that minimizes the need for extensive sanding.</p><h2>Advanced Control for Every Coat</h2><p>Whether you are applying the initial base coat or performing final touch-ups, the Platinum Finishing Box offers the versatility required for multi-stage finishing. The integrated crown adjustment dial provides granular control over the amount of compound dispensed, allowing you to tailor the thickness to your specific project needs. Combined with a high-performance pivoting axle, this tool adapts to the surface contours of your walls, ensuring uniform coverage and superior results across every seam.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Precision Dispensing:</strong> Automatically applies the ideal volume of joint compound for consistent, professional-grade results.</li><li><strong>Efficient Feathering:</strong> Simultaneously applies and feathers edges on flat and butt joints to save time on every pass.</li><li><strong>Adjustable Crown Dial:</strong> Easily modify the compound thickness to accommodate different stages of the finishing process.</li><li><strong>Pivoting Axle Design:</strong> Enhances maneuverability and ensures the blade maintains optimal contact with the wall surface.</li><li><strong>Professional Durability:</strong> Built to withstand the rigors of daily job site use while maintaining high-precision performance.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-10FB | | Tool Type | Flat Finishing Box | | Size | 10 Inches | | Application | Drywall Joint Finishing | | Price | $195.00 |</p>","The Platinum 10"" Flat Finishing Box applies compound and feathers edges of butt joints and flat joints in one pass. Features adjustable crown dial and pivoting axle.",195.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-10FB_7316520b.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-10fb",1403,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-FB12,,"12"" Flat Finishing Box",simple,"<h2>Achieve Professional Drywall Perfection</h2><p>Elevate your drywall finishing workflow with the Platinum 12"" Flat Finishing Box. Engineered for contractors who demand precision and efficiency, this tool streamlines the application of joint compound, ensuring a consistent, high-quality finish on every seam. Whether you are tackling a large-scale commercial project or a residential renovation, this finishing box provides the control and reliability needed to produce seamless walls with minimal effort.</p><h2>Advanced Engineering for Superior Results</h2><p>This second-generation finishing box is built to outperform standard industry tools. The integrated adjustable crown dial allows for granular control over compound thickness, enabling you to dial in the perfect amount for base coats or final finishes. To combat the challenges of imperfect framing, the precision-engineered pivoting axle automatically adjusts to surface irregularities, preventing skips and ensuring a smooth, level application across the entire span of the joint.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Adjustable Crown Control:</strong> Fine-tune your compound application with a simple dial adjustment, perfect for transitioning between initial fill coats and final skimming.</li><li><strong>Pivoting Axle Technology:</strong> Automatically compensates for uneven drywall surfaces, delivering a professional-grade finish even on challenging substrates.</li><li><strong>Simplified Maintenance:</strong> The innovative removable door plate design replaces outdated hinge systems, allowing for rapid disassembly and thorough cleaning after every job.</li><li><strong>Universal Compatibility:</strong> Designed with versatility in mind, all wear parts are compatible with most major industry-standard finishing boxes, ensuring long-term serviceability.</li><li><strong>Rugged Construction:</strong> Built to withstand the rigors of daily job site use, providing consistent performance and durability for the professional finisher.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-FB12 | | Tool Type | 12"" Flat Finishing Box | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Price | $205.00 | | Compatibility | Universal (Major Industry Brands) |</p>","The Platinum 12"" Flat Finishing Box features a second-generation design with removable door plate, adjustable crown dial, and pivoting axle. Wear parts compatible with most major brands.",205.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-FB12_1778f435.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-fb12",1404,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-14FB,,"14"" Flat Finishing Box",simple,"<h2>Professional-Grade Precision for Seamless Drywall Finishing</h2><p>Achieve a flawless, mirror-smooth finish on every seam with the Platinum 14"" Flat Finishing Box. Engineered for the professional contractor who demands consistency and speed, this high-capacity tool streamlines the taping and finishing process, significantly reducing manual labor time. Its robust construction ensures it can withstand the rigors of daily job site use while delivering the precise mud application required for high-end residential and commercial projects.</p><h2>Optimized for Efficiency and Control</h2><p>The 14-inch width provides an ideal footprint for covering wide joints and feathering edges with minimal effort. By maintaining a consistent mud flow and pressure, this finishing box eliminates the common inconsistencies associated with hand-tooling, allowing you to achieve a professional level of flatness that is ready for sanding and painting. The ergonomic design ensures that even during extended use, the tool remains balanced and easy to maneuver across walls and ceilings.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>High-Capacity Design:</strong> The 14-inch width allows for maximum coverage per pass, drastically increasing your daily output.</li><li><strong>Consistent Mud Application:</strong> Precision-engineered gates ensure an even distribution of compound, reducing the need for touch-ups.</li><li><strong>Durable Build Quality:</strong> Crafted from premium materials to resist wear and tear in demanding construction environments.</li><li><strong>Professional Finish:</strong> Designed to produce a smooth, feathered edge that minimizes sanding time and improves final paint results.</li><li><strong>User-Centric Ergonomics:</strong> Balanced weight distribution reduces operator fatigue during long finishing sessions.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-14FB | | Tool Type | Flat Finishing Box | | Width | 14 inches | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Price | $215.00 |</p>","The Platinum 14"" Flat Finishing Box applies compound and feathers edges in one pass. Features adjustable crown dial, pivoting axle, and universal handle compatibility.",215.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-14FB_9633c392.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-14fb",1405,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-2NS,,"2"" Nail Spotter",simple,"<h2>Precision Finishing for Every Fastener</h2><p>Elevate your drywall finishing workflow with the Platinum 2"" Nail Spotter. Engineered specifically for the demands of professional contractors, this compact, high-performance tool streamlines the process of coating nail and screw heads. By delivering a consistent, uniform finish in a single pass, it eliminates the need for tedious manual touch-ups, allowing you to achieve a flawless, paint-ready surface with unmatched speed and efficiency.</p><h2>Built for the Job Site</h2><p>Constructed from premium-grade anodized aluminum, this tool is designed to withstand the rigors of daily professional use while remaining lightweight and easy to maneuver. The integrated steel blade ensures a clean, sharp finish, while the high-quality urethane door seal provides a reliable, leak-free operation. With its smooth-glide wheel system, the Platinum Nail Spotter offers effortless tracking, ensuring you maintain professional-grade results from the first fastener to the last.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Professional Efficiency:</strong> Designed to rapidly coat nail and screw heads, significantly reducing labor time on large-scale drywall projects.</li><li><strong>Durable Construction:</strong> Crafted from high-grade anodized aluminum for superior corrosion resistance and long-term structural integrity.</li><li><strong>Precision Blade:</strong> Equipped with a hardened steel blade to ensure a clean, flush finish every time.</li><li><strong>Reliable Sealing:</strong> Features a high-performance urethane door seal to prevent leakage and maintain consistent pressure.</li><li><strong>Smooth Operation:</strong> Engineered with precision-glide wheels for steady, fluid movement across wall surfaces.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-2NS | | Tool Type | 2"" Nail Spotter | | Material | Anodized Aluminum / Steel | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Price | $160.00 |</p>","The Platinum 2"" Nail Spotter provides fast, consistent coating over nail and screw heads. High-grade anodized aluminum body, urethane door seal, and steel blade.",160.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-2NS_f1a9da8a.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-2ns",1406,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-CF2.5,,"2.5"" Angle Head with Wheels",simple,"<h2>Achieve Flawless Inside Corners with Precision Engineering</h2><p>Elevate your drywall finishing standards with the Platinum 2.5"" Angle Head. Designed for professionals who demand consistency and speed, this robust tool streamlines the process of finishing inside corners. By applying a uniform coat of compound to both sides of a corner simultaneously, it eliminates the need for tedious manual touch-ups, ensuring a crisp, professional edge that is ready for a final sand and paint.</p><h2>Superior Performance and Durability</h2><p>Constructed from high-grade cast aluminum, this angle head is built to withstand the rigors of daily job site use while maintaining its structural integrity. The integrated wheel system allows for effortless gliding, whether you are utilizing it in tandem with a corner roller or mounting it to a corner box. Its intuitive design reduces operator fatigue and significantly increases productivity, making it an essential asset for any high-efficiency drywall finishing workflow.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Precision Finishing:</strong> Simultaneously coats and finishes both sides of an inside corner for a perfectly sharp, uniform result.</li><li><strong>Durable Construction:</strong> Crafted from premium cast aluminum to ensure long-term reliability and resistance to wear.</li><li><strong>Smooth Operation:</strong> Integrated wheels provide a consistent, fluid motion across various surfaces, minimizing drag and maximizing control.</li><li><strong>Versatile Compatibility:</strong> Engineered to perform seamlessly when used with corner rollers or corner boxes for a complete finishing system.</li><li><strong>Time-Saving Efficiency:</strong> Dramatically reduces the time spent on manual corner detailing, allowing for a faster transition to the painting phase.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-CF2.5 | | Tool Type | Angle Head / Corner Finisher | | Size | 2.5 inches | | Material | Cast Aluminum | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools |</p>","Platinum 2.5"" Angle Head Corner Finisher with cast-aluminum design for smooth inside corners in a single pass. Compatible with corner rollers and corner boxes.",239.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-CF2.5_a6afa209.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-cf2.5",1407,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-CT24,,"24"" Compound Tube",simple,"<h2>Precision Drywall Finishing Made Simple</h2><p>Elevate your drywall finishing workflow with the Platinum 24"" Compound Tube. Engineered for professionals who demand efficiency and precision, this tool streamlines the application of joint compound across internal corners, external corners, and flat surfaces. By utilizing a specialized applicator head (sold separately), you can achieve consistent, professional-grade results with significantly less effort than manual methods.</p><h2>Designed for Maneuverability and Speed</h2><p>As the most compact model in the Platinum lineup, the 24"" Compound Tube is the ideal solution for navigating tight spaces and intricate architectural details. Its intuitive, syringe-style loading mechanism allows for rapid refilling directly from your compound bucket, minimizing downtime and keeping you focused on the task at hand. Built to withstand the rigors of the job site, this tube is an essential investment for contractors looking to accelerate their finishing speed without compromising on quality.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Versatile Application:</strong> Compatible with a variety of applicator heads to handle corners and flat joints with ease.</li><li><strong>Efficient Loading System:</strong> Operates like a high-capacity syringe for quick, mess-free suction of joint compound.</li><li><strong>Compact 24-Inch Design:</strong> Perfectly sized for superior control in confined areas and detailed finishing work.</li><li><strong>Professional-Grade Durability:</strong> Constructed with robust materials to ensure long-term reliability in demanding environments.</li><li><strong>Workflow Optimization:</strong> Significantly reduces the time required for manual compound application, boosting overall project productivity.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-CT24 | | Tool Type | Compound Tube | | Length | 24 inches | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Price | $150.00 |</p>","The Platinum 24"" Compound Tube applies joint compound to corners and flats with an applicator head (sold separately). Compact size ideal for tight areas.",150.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-CT24_3025470f.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-ct24",1408,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-3CF,,"3"" Angle Head Corner Finisher with Wheels",simple,"<h2>Achieve Flawless Inside Corners with Precision</h2><p>Elevate your drywall finishing workflow with the Platinum 3"" Angle Head Corner Finisher. Engineered for the professional contractor who demands efficiency and consistency, this tool streamlines the glazing and finishing process. By simultaneously feathering both sides of an inside corner in one fluid motion, it eliminates the need for tedious manual touch-ups, ensuring a professional-grade surface that is ready for paint with minimal sanding.</p><h2>Built for the Job Site</h2><p>Durability meets performance in this robust mechanical flusher. Crafted from a premium blend of high-grade stainless steel and lightweight aluminum, the PT-3CF is designed to withstand the rigors of daily use in demanding environments. Its smooth-gliding wheel system ensures effortless tracking along the corner, providing a consistent, uniform finish that meets the high standards of modern drywall installation.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Dual-Sided Efficiency:</strong> Simultaneously finishes both sides of an inside corner, significantly reducing labor time and increasing productivity.</li><li><strong>Professional Finish:</strong> Delivers a smooth, feathered edge that minimizes sanding requirements and prepares surfaces perfectly for final painting.</li><li><strong>Premium Construction:</strong> Built with a combination of stainless steel and aluminum for maximum longevity and resistance to wear.</li><li><strong>Industry Standard Size:</strong> The 3-inch width is the preferred choice for professionals, ideal for both glazing and final finish coats.</li><li><strong>Universal Compatibility:</strong> Designed to integrate seamlessly with all major drywall finishing handles and equipment.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-3CF | | Tool Type | Angle Head Corner Finisher | | Size | 3 inches | | Material | Stainless Steel and Aluminum | | Application | Glazing and Finish Coats | | Price | $249.00 |</p>","The Platinum 3"" Angle Head Corner Finisher evenly finishes both sides of inside corners in one pass. Stainless steel and aluminum construction for long service life.",249.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-3CF_de71f33d.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-3cf",1409,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-3NS,,"3"" Nail Spotter",simple,"<h2>Precision Finishing for Every Fastener</h2><p>Achieve a flawless, professional-grade finish on your drywall projects with the Platinum 3"" Nail Spotter. Engineered for efficiency and durability, this specialized tool acts as a compact flat box, specifically designed to coat and conceal nail and screw heads with ease. Whether you are a seasoned contractor or a dedicated professional, this tool streamlines your workflow, ensuring consistent results and a smooth surface ready for the final coat.</p><h2>Built for the Job Site</h2><p>Constructed from high-grade anodized aluminum, the Platinum 3"" Nail Spotter is built to withstand the rigors of daily use while remaining lightweight and maneuverable. The inclusion of a robust carbide steel blade ensures long-lasting sharpness and precision, while the high-quality urethane door seal prevents leaks and maintains optimal pressure. Designed with the user in mind, this tool is exceptionally easy to operate and maintain, allowing for quick cleanup after a long day on the job.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Durable Construction:</strong> Features a high-grade anodized aluminum body for superior longevity and resistance to wear.</li><li><strong>Precision Blade:</strong> Equipped with a carbide steel blade that provides a clean, consistent finish every time.</li><li><strong>Leak-Resistant Design:</strong> Integrated urethane door seal ensures material stays where it belongs, minimizing waste and mess.</li><li><strong>Smooth Operation:</strong> High-performance glide wheels allow the tool to move effortlessly across drywall surfaces.</li><li><strong>Universal Compatibility:</strong> The threaded end is designed to fit seamlessly onto any standard corner roller handle, offering versatile integration into your existing tool kit.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-3NS | | Tool Type | 3"" Nail Spotter | | Material | Anodized Aluminum, Carbide Steel | | Seal Material | Urethane | | Compatibility | Standard Corner Roller Handles | | Price | $160.00 |</p>","The Platinum 3"" Nail Spotter features an anodized aluminum body, urethane door seal, smooth glide wheels, and carbide steel blade. Fits standard corner roller handles.",160.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-2NS_f1a9da8a.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-3ns",1410,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-CF3.5,,"3.5"" Angle Head Corner Finisher with Wheels",simple,"<h2>Achieve Professional-Grade Inside Corners with Ease</h2><p>Elevate your drywall finishing workflow with the Platinum 3.5"" Angle Head Corner Finisher. Engineered for contractors who demand precision and efficiency, this tool streamlines the process of feathering and finishing inside corners. By applying a consistent, smooth coat to both sides of a corner simultaneously, it eliminates the need for tedious manual touch-ups and ensures a uniform, professional result every time.</p><h2>Precision Engineering for Superior Results</h2><p>Constructed from high-grade cast aluminum, this corner finisher is built to withstand the rigors of daily job site use while maintaining its structural integrity. The integrated wheel system ensures effortless gliding across the wall surface, reducing operator fatigue and promoting a steady, controlled application. Whether you are pairing this tool with a corner roller or utilizing it in conjunction with a corner box, you can expect a sharp, clean finish that requires minimal sanding before painting.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Dual-Sided Efficiency:</strong> Simultaneously finishes both sides of an inside corner in one fluid motion, significantly increasing productivity.</li><li><strong>Durable Construction:</strong> Features a robust, high-quality cast-aluminum body designed for long-term reliability and consistent performance.</li><li><strong>Smooth Operation:</strong> Equipped with precision wheels that allow for seamless movement, ensuring a streak-free and professional application.</li><li><strong>Versatile Compatibility:</strong> Perfectly suited for use with corner rollers or corner boxes to achieve a flawless, paint-ready finish.</li><li><strong>Time-Saving Design:</strong> Dramatically reduces the time spent on manual corner finishing and sanding, allowing for faster project completion.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-CF3.5 | | Tool Type | Angle Head Corner Finisher | | Size | 3.5 inches | | Material | Cast Aluminum | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Price | $259.00 |</p>","Platinum 3.5"" Angle Head Corner Finisher with cast-aluminum design for sharp, paintable inside corners. Compatible with corner rollers and corner boxes.",259.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-CF3.5_4018902b.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-cf3.5",1411,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-BH34,,"34"" Flat Box Handle",simple,"<h2>Elevate Your Finishing Precision</h2><p>Master your drywall projects with the Platinum 34"" Flat Box Handle, an essential tool engineered for the modern professional. Designed to bridge the gap between heavy-duty durability and lightweight maneuverability, this handle ensures that every pass is smooth, consistent, and effortless. Whether you are tackling residential renovations or large-scale commercial contracts, this tool provides the reliability required to maintain high-quality standards throughout the workday.</p><h2>Engineered for Performance and Comfort</h2><p>Constructed from premium anodized aluminum, this handle offers an exceptional strength-to-weight ratio, significantly reducing operator fatigue during extended finishing sessions. The integrated ergonomic grip is fully adjustable, allowing for a customized fit that enhances control and reduces strain. With its advanced full-motion braking system, you gain precise command over your flat box, ensuring seamless application and professional-grade results on every wall and ceiling.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Professional-Grade Construction:</strong> Crafted from high-strength anodized aluminum for long-term durability in demanding jobsite environments.</li><li><strong>Advanced Braking System:</strong> Features a sophisticated full-motion brake mechanism that provides superior responsiveness and control compared to traditional designs.</li><li><strong>Ergonomic Design:</strong> Includes an adjustable grip to accommodate various hand sizes and preferences, promoting comfort during repetitive tasks.</li><li><strong>Optimized Length:</strong> The 34-inch reach is perfectly calibrated for standard wall heights, offering the ideal balance of leverage and maneuverability.</li><li><strong>Lightweight Build:</strong> Minimizes physical exertion, allowing for increased productivity and reduced downtime due to fatigue.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-BH34 | | Product Type | Flat Box Handle | | Material | Anodized Aluminum | | Length | 34 inches | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Price | $90.00 |</p>","The Platinum 34"" Flat Box Handle is built from lightweight anodized aluminum with ergonomic grip and advanced full-motion braking mechanism.",90.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-BH34_366378ac.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-bh34",1412,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-CT36,,"36"" Compound Tube",simple,"<h2>Elevate Your Drywall Finishing Efficiency</h2><p>Streamline your workflow and achieve professional-grade results with the Platinum 36"" Compound Tube. Engineered for the demands of high-volume drywall finishing, this robust tool acts as a high-capacity delivery system, allowing you to apply joint compound to internal corners, external corners, and flat surfaces with unparalleled speed and consistency. By integrating this tube into your toolkit, you significantly reduce the time spent on manual application, ensuring a cleaner, more uniform finish across every project.</p><h2>Precision Engineering for Professional Results</h2><p>Designed with the professional contractor in mind, the Platinum 36"" Compound Tube functions with the simplicity and reliability of a heavy-duty syringe. Its intuitive design allows for rapid loading directly from your compound bucket, minimizing downtime and mess. The 36-inch length is specifically optimized for maneuverability, providing the perfect balance of reach and control when navigating tight spaces or complex architectural details. Built to withstand the rigors of daily job-site use, this tool is an essential investment for any finisher looking to maximize productivity without sacrificing quality.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>High-Capacity Application:</strong> Rapidly draws and dispenses joint compound, drastically cutting down on manual labor time.</li><li><strong>Versatile Compatibility:</strong> Designed to work seamlessly with a variety of applicator heads (sold separately) for corners and flats.</li><li><strong>Optimized Reach:</strong> The 36-inch frame offers the ideal length for accessing hard-to-reach areas while maintaining precise control.</li><li><strong>Durable Construction:</strong> Engineered with premium materials to ensure long-term reliability and consistent performance under heavy use.</li><li><strong>User-Friendly Operation:</strong> Simple pull-handle mechanism allows for quick, effortless filling and smooth compound distribution.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-CT36 | | Product Type | Compound Tube | | Length | 36 inches | | Application | Internal/External Corners and Flats | | Price | $155.00 |</p>","The Platinum 36"" Compound Tube applies joint compound to corners and flats with an applicator head (sold separately). Well-built for high productivity.",155.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-CT36_519f96aa.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-ct36",1413,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-AICA,,4 Wheel Inside Angle / Corner Applicator,simple,"<h2>Achieve Flawless Inside Corners with Precision</h2><p>Elevate your drywall finishing standards with the Platinum 4-Wheel Inside Angle Applicator. Engineered for professionals who demand speed without sacrificing quality, this tool streamlines the taping process, ensuring that every inside corner is finished with professional-grade consistency. By reducing the need for manual touch-ups, this applicator significantly boosts your daily productivity on the job site.</p><h2>Superior Design for Seamless Results</h2><p>The standout feature of this applicator is its specialized four-wheel configuration, which provides unparalleled stability and tracking as you move along wall joints. This design allows the tool to glide smoothly over various surfaces, preventing the common skips and uneven mud distribution found with inferior equipment. Constructed from premium, high-durability materials, it is built to withstand the rigorous demands of daily construction environments.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Four-Wheel Stability:</strong> The advanced wheel system ensures the applicator stays centered and balanced, delivering a uniform coat of compound every time.</li><li><strong>Effortless Maneuverability:</strong> Designed to glide across inside angles, minimizing operator fatigue during long finishing sessions.</li><li><strong>Universal Compatibility:</strong> Engineered to work seamlessly with a wide range of corner bead types and sizes, offering maximum versatility for diverse project requirements.</li><li><strong>Professional-Grade Durability:</strong> Crafted from high-quality components to ensure long-term reliability and consistent performance under heavy use.</li><li><strong>Efficiency Focused:</strong> Significantly reduces finishing time, allowing for faster project turnaround without compromising on the final aesthetic.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-AICA | | Product Type | 4-Wheel Inside Angle / Corner Applicator | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Price | $89.00 |</p>",The Platinum 4-Wheel Inside Angle/Corner Applicator makes taping and finishing inside angles and corners easy and efficient. Compatible with various corner bead types.,89.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-AICA_c3a12474.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-aica",1414,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-FA,,"4"" Flat Applicator",simple,"<h2>Achieve Flawless Drywall Finishes with Precision</h2><p>Elevate your finishing workflow with the Platinum 4"" Flat Applicator. Engineered for professionals who demand consistency and speed, this tool is designed to deliver smooth, uniform compound application across flat joints. Whether you are working on residential renovations or large-scale commercial projects, this applicator provides the reliability needed to achieve a professional-grade finish with every pass.</p><h2>Built for Performance and Durability</h2><p>Constructed to withstand the rigors of daily job site use, the Platinum Flat Applicator balances lightweight handling with robust structural integrity. Its ergonomic design minimizes operator fatigue during extended use, while the precision-engineered blade ensures optimal compound distribution, significantly reducing the need for excessive sanding or rework. This is an essential addition to any drywall finisher's toolkit, streamlining your process and enhancing overall project quality.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Precision Application:</strong> Engineered to lay down a consistent, even layer of joint compound for seamless finishing.</li><li><strong>Professional Grade:</strong> Designed specifically for the demands of high-volume drywall installation and repair.</li><li><strong>Ergonomic Design:</strong> Optimized for comfort and control, allowing for steady, fluid motions across flat surfaces.</li><li><strong>Durable Construction:</strong> Built with high-quality materials to ensure longevity and consistent performance under heavy use.</li><li><strong>Efficiency Focused:</strong> Reduces application time and material waste, helping you complete projects faster and more profitably.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-FA | | Tool Type | Flat Applicator | | Size | 4 Inches | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Price | $59.00 |</p>","Platinum 4"" Flat Applicator for compact seam finishing. Compatible with standard flat box handles from major brands.",59.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-FA_c3f41750.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-fa",1415,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-CT42,,"42"" Compound Tube",simple,"<h2>Professional-Grade Precision for Drywall Finishing</h2><p>Elevate your drywall finishing workflow with the Platinum 42"" Compound Tube. Engineered for the demanding professional, this tool is designed to streamline the application of joint compound, ensuring consistent, high-quality results across every seam. Its robust construction provides the reliability needed for high-volume job sites, allowing you to work faster and with greater accuracy than traditional manual methods.</p><h2>Built for Efficiency and Control</h2><p>This compound tube is an essential asset for contractors looking to minimize fatigue and maximize output. The 42-inch length offers an ideal reach for standard wall heights, reducing the need for constant repositioning. By delivering a controlled flow of compound directly to your finishing heads, this tool helps maintain a clean workspace and significantly reduces material waste, making it a smart investment for any professional drywall toolkit.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Optimized Reach:</strong> The 42-inch design provides excellent coverage for walls and ceilings, minimizing the need for ladders or stilts.</li><li><strong>Durable Construction:</strong> Built with high-quality materials to withstand the rigors of daily professional use.</li><li><strong>Consistent Flow:</strong> Engineered for smooth, reliable compound delivery to ensure a uniform finish every time.</li><li><strong>Ergonomic Design:</strong> Balanced for comfort, allowing for extended use with reduced physical strain.</li><li><strong>Seamless Integration:</strong> Compatible with standard industry finishing heads for versatile application.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-CT42 | | Product Type | Compound Tube | | Length | 42 inches | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Price | $160.00 |</p>","Platinum 42"" Compound Tube for reaching high walls and ceilings. Works with all major brand applicator heads (sold separately).",160.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-CT42_1869f3d1.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-ct42",1416,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-BH42,,"42"" Flat Box Handle",simple,"<h2>Elevate Your Drywall Finishing Precision</h2><p>Achieve professional-grade results with the Platinum 42-inch Flat Box Handle, an essential tool engineered for high-output drywall contractors. Designed to bridge the gap between reach and maneuverability, this handle provides the stability required for flawless seams on both walls and ceilings. By utilizing premium materials and an intuitive design, it empowers finishers to maintain high standards of quality throughout demanding workdays.</p><h2>Built for Performance and Longevity</h2><p>Constructed from high-grade anodized aluminum, this handle offers a superior strength-to-weight ratio. The lightweight profile significantly reduces operator fatigue, allowing for extended periods of use without sacrificing control. The fixed 42-inch length ensures a consistent, reliable feel, eliminating the mechanical play often found in adjustable models and providing a direct, responsive connection to your flat box.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Professional-Grade Construction:</strong> Crafted from durable, anodized aluminum to withstand the rigors of daily job site use while resisting corrosion.</li><li><strong>Optimized Length:</strong> The fixed 42-inch design offers the perfect balance of reach for high walls and ceilings while maintaining excellent leverage for lower applications.</li><li><strong>Ergonomic Handling:</strong> Features a comfortable grip designed to minimize hand strain and improve maneuverability during repetitive finishing strokes.</li><li><strong>Secure Attachment System:</strong> Engineered for a rock-solid connection to your flat box, ensuring smooth, chatter-free operation and consistent mud application.</li><li><strong>Fatigue Reduction:</strong> The lightweight architecture allows for precise, fluid movements, helping you maintain productivity from start to finish.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-BH42 | | Material | Anodized Aluminum | | Handle Length | 42 inches | | Tool Type | Flat Box Handle | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Price | $95.00 |</p>","The Platinum 42"" Flat Box Handle is built from lightweight anodized aluminum with ergonomic grip and secure attachment design for consistent flat box results.",95.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-BH34_e35382a4.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-bh42",1417,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-CFH50,,"50"" Angle Head Handle",simple,"<h2>Elevate Your Finishing Precision</h2><p>Achieve flawless corner finishes with the Platinum 50"" Angle Head Handle, a professional-grade tool engineered for durability and superior control. Designed specifically for drywall contractors who demand consistency, this handle provides the reach and stability necessary to tackle high-wall corners and ceilings with ease, reducing fatigue during extended shifts.</p><h2>Built for the Professional</h2><p>Constructed from high-strength, anodized aluminum, this handle is built to withstand the rigors of a demanding job site while remaining lightweight enough for precision maneuvering. The ergonomic rubber grip ensures a secure, comfortable hold, while the integrated adjustable ball grip allows you to fine-tune your leverage, providing the exact level of tension required for smooth, professional-grade corner application.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Durable Construction:</strong> Crafted from premium anodized aluminum to resist corrosion and job-site wear.</li><li><strong>Extended Reach:</strong> The 50-inch length provides optimal access for high-ceiling and hard-to-reach corner finishing.</li><li><strong>Ergonomic Control:</strong> Features a high-traction rubber grip for maximum comfort and reduced hand strain.</li><li><strong>Adjustable Ball Grip:</strong> Offers customizable tension and control for precise angle head operation.</li><li><strong>Professional Reliability:</strong> Engineered for consistent performance, ensuring a long service life in professional drywall environments.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-CFH50 | | Material | Anodized Aluminum | | Length | 50 inches | | Grip Type | Rubber / Adjustable Ball Grip | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools |</p>","The Platinum 50"" Angle Head Handle is a heavy-duty anodized aluminum handle with rubber grip and adjustable ball grip. Built to last.",49.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-CFH50_2081ebeb.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-cfh50",1418,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-CAH50,,"50"" Corner Box Handle",simple,"<h2>Elevate Your Drywall Finishing Precision</h2><p>Achieve seamless corner finishes with the Platinum 50"" Corner Box Handle. Engineered for professionals who demand consistency and reach, this tool is an essential addition to your drywall finishing arsenal. Its robust construction ensures reliable performance during high-volume projects, allowing you to tackle tall walls and hard-to-reach corners with ease and ergonomic comfort.</p><h2>Designed for Professional Efficiency</h2><p>This handle is built to integrate perfectly with your existing corner box system, providing the leverage and control necessary for a smooth, professional-grade application of joint compound. By extending your reach, it minimizes the need for ladders or stilts, significantly improving your workflow efficiency and safety on the job site. The lightweight yet durable design reduces operator fatigue, ensuring you can maintain high-quality results throughout the entire workday.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Extended Reach:</strong> The 50-inch length provides optimal access to high corners and ceilings without the need for additional climbing equipment.</li><li><strong>Ergonomic Control:</strong> Designed to provide a secure, comfortable grip, allowing for precise pressure application and consistent compound distribution.</li><li><strong>Professional Durability:</strong> Constructed from high-quality materials to withstand the rigors of daily construction site use.</li><li><strong>Seamless Compatibility:</strong> Specifically engineered to work with standard corner boxes, ensuring a quick and secure attachment for immediate use.</li><li><strong>Enhanced Workflow:</strong> Streamlines the finishing process, saving time and effort on both residential and commercial drywall installations.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-CAH50 | | Product Type | Corner Box Handle | | Length | 50 inches | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Price | $49.00 |</p>","Platinum 50"" Corner Box Handle — heavy-duty anodized aluminum with rubber grip and adjustable ball grip. Compatible with all major corner box brands.",49.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-CAH50_6fb3f7b9.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-cah50",1419,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-CRH50,,"50"" Corner Roller Handle",simple,"<h2>Master Precision Corner Finishing</h2><p>Elevate your drywall finishing workflow with the Platinum 50"" Corner Roller Handle. Engineered for professionals who demand consistency and durability, this tool provides the extended reach necessary to tackle high-wall corners and ceilings with ease. By combining robust construction with ergonomic design, it minimizes operator fatigue while ensuring a flawless, professional-grade finish on every corner.</p><h2>Built for the Job Site</h2><p>Constructed from high-grade anodized aluminum, this handle is designed to withstand the rigorous demands of daily professional use. The lightweight yet rigid frame ensures excellent power transfer, allowing for smooth, controlled application of corner rollers. With its 50-inch length, you gain the leverage and reach required to maintain productivity without the need for constant repositioning or unsafe ladder work.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Durable Anodized Finish:</strong> The heavy-duty aluminum construction resists corrosion and wear, ensuring a long service life in challenging job site environments.</li><li><strong>Extended Reach:</strong> At 50 inches in length, this handle is perfectly sized for reaching high corners and ceilings comfortably.</li><li><strong>Ergonomic Rubber Grip:</strong> The primary handle features a high-traction rubber grip, providing a secure hold even when hands are dusty or damp.</li><li><strong>Adjustable Ball Grip:</strong> Includes a secondary, adjustable ball grip that allows for precise pressure control and improved maneuverability during the finishing process.</li><li><strong>Professional Compatibility:</strong> Designed to integrate seamlessly with standard corner roller heads, making it an essential addition to any drywall finishing kit.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-CRH50 | | Product Type | Corner Roller Handle | | Material | Anodized Aluminum | | Length | 50 inches | | Grip Type | Rubberized / Adjustable Ball Grip | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools |</p>","The Platinum 50"" Corner Roller Handle is a heavy-duty anodized aluminum handle with rubber grip and adjustable ball grip. Built to last.",59.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-CRH50_d5c4f30d.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-crh50",1420,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-BH54,,"54"" Flat Box Handle",simple,"<h2>Elevate Your Finishing Efficiency</h2><p>Take command of your drywall finishing projects with the Platinum 54"" Flat Box Handle. Engineered for professionals who demand both reach and reliability, this tool bridges the gap between high-wall accessibility and ergonomic comfort. By utilizing advanced materials and a refined braking system, it ensures that your workflow remains smooth, consistent, and fatigue-free, even during extended shifts.</p><h2>Precision Control and Extended Reach</h2><p>Designed specifically for high-ceiling applications and expansive wall surfaces, this 54-inch handle provides the leverage you need without the bulk. The lightweight anodized aluminum construction minimizes physical strain, while the integrated braking mechanism delivers superior, full-range control. Unlike legacy designs that offer limited stopping power, this modern handle allows for precise adjustments, giving you the confidence to achieve a flawless finish every time.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Extended Reach:</strong> The 54-inch length is optimized for high walls and ceilings, reducing the need for ladders and scaffolding.</li><li><strong>Lightweight Durability:</strong> Crafted from premium anodized aluminum to provide a robust, corrosion-resistant build that won't weigh you down.</li><li><strong>Advanced Braking System:</strong> Features a full-motion braking mechanism that offers superior control and responsiveness compared to traditional handles.</li><li><strong>Ergonomic Design:</strong> Includes an adjustable grip tailored to enhance user comfort and reduce hand fatigue during repetitive tasks.</li><li><strong>Professional Grade:</strong> Built to withstand the rigors of daily job site use, ensuring long-term performance and value.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-BH54 | | Handle Length | 54 inches | | Material | Anodized Aluminum | | Product Type | Flat Box Handle | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools |</p>","The Platinum 54"" Flat Box Handle is lightweight anodized aluminum with adjustable grip and full-motion braking. Ideal for high ceilings and walls.",100.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-BH54_ab8ebcad.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-bh54",1421,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-CA8,,"8"" Corner Applicator",simple,"<h2>Elevate Your Drywall Finishing Efficiency</h2><p>Achieve flawless internal corner finishes with the Platinum 8"" Corner Applicator. Engineered for professional drywall contractors who demand speed and precision, this high-capacity tool streamlines the application of joint compound, ensuring consistent results across every run. By maximizing your output, this applicator reduces downtime and helps you complete projects with professional-grade accuracy.</p><h2>Built for Performance and Longevity</h2><p>Constructed from premium anodized aluminum, the Platinum 8"" Corner Applicator strikes the perfect balance between rugged durability and lightweight maneuverability. Its high-capacity design allows for extended operation without the need for constant refilling, significantly boosting your daily productivity. Designed with versatility in mind, this unit is fully compatible with all major industry-standard angle heads, making it an essential addition to any professional finishing kit.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>High-Capacity Design:</strong> The 8-inch box holds more compound, allowing for longer, uninterrupted runs and fewer trips to the pump.</li><li><strong>Durable Construction:</strong> Crafted from anodized aluminum to withstand the rigors of daily job site use while remaining lightweight for reduced operator fatigue.</li><li><strong>Extended Reach:</strong> Includes a 50-inch standard corner box handle, providing the necessary leverage and reach for high ceilings and hard-to-access corners.</li><li><strong>Universal Compatibility:</strong> Engineered to integrate seamlessly with all major brands of angle heads, ensuring a versatile fit for your existing tool inventory.</li><li><strong>Professional Precision:</strong> Delivers a smooth, uniform application of joint compound, setting the stage for a perfect finish every time.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-CA8 | | Tool Type | Corner Applicator | | Material | Anodized Aluminum | | Handle Length | 50 inches | | Capacity | 8 inches | | Compatibility | Universal (Fits all major angle head brands) |</p>","The Platinum 8"" Corner Applicator applies joint compound to internal corners with an angle head. High-capacity 8"" box for longer runs and higher productivity.",159.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-CA8_5a7ff95c.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-ca8",1422,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-8FB,,"8"" Flat Finishing Box",simple,"<h2>Achieve Flawless Drywall Finishes with Precision</h2><p>Elevate your drywall installation workflow with the Platinum 8"" Flat Finishing Box. Engineered for professionals who demand consistency and speed, this tool streamlines the application of joint compound, ensuring a smooth, uniform finish across every seam. By automating the distribution of mud, this finishing box significantly reduces manual labor and minimizes the need for extensive sanding, allowing you to achieve a professional-grade result in a fraction of the time.</p><h2>Built for Performance and Reliability</h2><p>Designed to withstand the rigors of high-volume job sites, the Platinum 8"" Flat Finishing Box is constructed from durable, high-quality materials that resist wear and corrosion. Its ergonomic design provides excellent control and balance, reducing operator fatigue during extended use. Whether you are tackling residential renovations or large-scale commercial projects, this tool offers the precision required to meet the highest industry standards for wall and ceiling finishing.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Consistent Compound Application:</strong> Delivers a precise, even layer of joint compound for a superior finish every time.</li><li><strong>Increased Efficiency:</strong> Dramatically accelerates the taping and finishing process compared to traditional hand-tooling methods.</li><li><strong>Durable Construction:</strong> Built with robust materials to ensure long-term reliability in demanding professional environments.</li><li><strong>Ergonomic Handling:</strong> Balanced design promotes ease of use and reduces physical strain during repetitive tasks.</li><li><strong>Professional Results:</strong> Minimizes surface imperfections, creating a seamless base for paint or wallpaper application.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-8FB | | Tool Type | Flat Finishing Box | | Size | 8 Inches | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Price | $185.00 |</p>","The Platinum 8"" Flat Finishing Box applies compound and feathers edges in one pass. Adjustable crown dial and pivoting axle for consistent, professional results.",185.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-8FB_e544b8c4.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-8fb",1423,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-BF,,Box Filler Attachment,simple,"<h2>Streamline Your Finishing Workflow</h2><p>Maximize the efficiency of your drywall finishing process with the Platinum Box Filler Attachment. Engineered for professionals who demand reliability on the job site, this essential accessory bridges the gap between your compound pump and your finishing tools. By providing a seamless, high-volume transfer of joint compound, it eliminates the mess and downtime associated with manual filling, allowing you to maintain a consistent pace throughout your workday.</p><h2>Precision Engineering for Heavy-Duty Use</h2><p>Crafted with durability at the forefront, this attachment is built to withstand the rigorous demands of daily professional use. Its robust construction ensures a secure, leak-free connection to your existing pump equipment, providing peace of mind when working with heavy-bodied compounds. Whether you are prepping for a large-scale commercial project or a detailed residential renovation, this tool offers the structural integrity required to perform under pressure.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Universal Compatibility:</strong> Designed to integrate effortlessly with all major brands of drywall compound pumps, ensuring a versatile addition to your existing tool kit.</li><li><strong>Multi-Tool Versatility:</strong> Perfectly suited for filling a wide range of finishing equipment, including flat boxes, corner applicators, and nail spotters.</li><li><strong>Rugged Construction:</strong> Handcrafted for superior longevity, this attachment is built to endure the wear and tear of high-frequency job site environments.</li><li><strong>Optimized Flow:</strong> Engineered to facilitate rapid, clean filling, significantly reducing material waste and saving valuable time during application.</li><li><strong>Secure Attachment:</strong> Features a reliable bolt-on design that maintains a stable, airtight seal for consistent performance across all your drywall finishing tasks.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-BF | | Product Type | Box Filler Attachment | | Compatibility | Universal (Major Drywall Pump Brands) | | Primary Use | Filling Flat Boxes, Corner Applicators, Nail Spotters | | Construction | Handcrafted Heavy-Duty Metal |</p>","The Platinum Box Filler Attachment connects to all major drywall compound pumps to fill flat boxes, corner applicators, and nail spotters.",49.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-BF_314fcef3.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-bf",1424,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-2.5CF,,"Corner Flusher 2.5""",simple,"<h2>Achieve Flawless Internal Corners with Precision</h2><p>Elevate your drywall finishing standards with the Platinum 2.5"" Corner Flusher. Engineered for professionals who demand consistency and speed, this tool is an essential addition to your finishing kit. Whether you are applying a smooth base coat or executing a final finish, this flusher ensures uniform compound distribution and crisp, clean angles every single time.</p><h2>Built for Durability and Performance</h2><p>Crafted from premium surgical-grade stainless spring steel, this tool is designed to withstand the rigors of daily job-site use without losing its shape. The high-tension steel construction provides the perfect amount of flex, allowing for seamless feathering and a professional-grade finish that minimizes the need for extensive sanding. Its universal compatibility ensures it integrates effortlessly with your existing inventory of angle head and flusher handles from all major industry brands.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Surgical Stainless Steel Construction:</strong> High-grade material ensures long-term durability, rust resistance, and consistent shape retention.</li><li><strong>Versatile Application:</strong> Optimized for both base coat and final finish coats to streamline your workflow.</li><li><strong>Universal Compatibility:</strong> Designed to fit seamlessly onto all standard major-brand angle head and flusher handles.</li><li><strong>Precision Engineering:</strong> Delivers a consistent 2.5-inch finish, ideal for standard internal corner applications.</li><li><strong>Professional Grade:</strong> Built to meet the high-performance requirements of drywall contractors and finishing specialists.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-2.5CF | | Tool Type | Corner Flusher | | Size | 2.5 inches | | Material | Surgical Stainless Spring Steel | | Compatibility | Universal (Major Brand Handles) | | Price | $75.00 |</p>","Platinum 2.5"" Corner Flusher in surgical stainless spring steel for base coat or finish coat. Fits all major brands of angle head or flusher handles.",75.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-2.5CF_ba37654f.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-2.5cf",1425,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,GN,,Drywall Gooseneck Adapter,simple,"<h2>Elevate Your Drywall Finishing Efficiency</h2><p>Streamline your workflow with the Platinum Drywall Tools Gooseneck, an essential precision attachment engineered for professional-grade compound pumps. Designed to bridge the gap between your pump and automatic taper, this adapter ensures a seamless, high-volume transfer of joint compound, allowing you to maintain momentum and precision throughout your workday.</p><h2>Built for the Demanding Jobsite</h2><p>Crafted from premium-grade stainless steel, this gooseneck is built to withstand the rigors of daily construction environments. Its robust construction offers superior resistance to corrosion and mechanical wear, ensuring that your equipment remains reliable project after project. The integrated taper rest is thoughtfully finished with protective rubber sleeves, safeguarding your automatic taper against surface marring, scratches, and premature wear during the filling process.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Precision Engineering:</strong> Specifically designed for seamless integration with standard compound pumps to optimize joint compound flow.</li><li><strong>Durable Construction:</strong> Manufactured from high-grade stainless steel for maximum longevity and resistance to jobsite elements.</li><li><strong>Equipment Protection:</strong> Features rubber-sleeved taper rests to prevent damage and maintain the finish of your automatic taper.</li><li><strong>Professional Performance:</strong> Enhances the speed and consistency of your drywall finishing setup.</li><li><strong>Reliable Compatibility:</strong> Engineered by Platinum to meet the rigorous standards of professional drywall contractors.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | GN | | Material | High-Grade Stainless Steel | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Protective Features | Rubber-sleeved taper rest | | Compatibility | Standard Compound Pumps |</p>",The Platinum Gooseneck Adapter fills automatic tapers from compound pumps. Made from high-grade stainless steel with rubber-sleeved taper rest.,59.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/GN_a054d56a.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, gn",1426,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-CP,,Drywall Pump w/Filler,simple,"<h2>Professional-Grade Efficiency for Drywall Finishing</h2><p>Elevate your workflow with the Platinum Drywall Loading Pump, a robust solution engineered for contractors who demand reliability and precision on the job site. Designed to streamline the filling process, this pump eliminates the downtime associated with manual loading, allowing you to maintain a consistent pace throughout your finishing projects.</p><h2>Built for Longevity and Performance</h2><p>Constructed from premium-grade anodized aluminum, this pump is built to withstand the rigors of daily professional use. The high-quality material selection ensures superior resistance to corrosion and wear, providing a long-lasting tool that maintains its integrity under demanding conditions. By prioritizing durable components, Platinum delivers a dependable piece of equipment that minimizes maintenance requirements and maximizes your return on investment.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Precision Engineering:</strong> Meticulously machined components ensure smooth operation and consistent output every time you use the pump.</li><li><strong>Corrosion-Resistant Build:</strong> The anodized aluminum housing protects against moisture and job site elements, significantly extending the tool's lifespan.</li><li><strong>Universal Compatibility:</strong> Includes a complimentary box filler attachment, allowing for seamless integration with all major brands of flat boxes, corner boxes, and nail spotters.</li><li><strong>Optimized Workflow:</strong> Designed to drastically reduce loading time, enabling faster transitions between finishing tasks.</li><li><strong>Professional Reliability:</strong> A trusted choice for drywall professionals looking to upgrade their equipment with a tool that balances performance with durability.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-CP | | Material | Anodized Aluminum | | Included Accessories | Box Filler Attachment | | Compatibility | Major brands of Flat Boxes, Corner Boxes, and Nail Spotters | | Price | $269.00 | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools |</p>",The Platinum Drywall Loading Pump is precision machined from anodized aluminum for long service life. Includes a free box filler attachment.,269.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-CP_18d98178.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-cp",1427,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-CRE,,ECO Inside Corner Roller,simple,"<h2>Achieve Flawless Inside Corners with Ease</h2><p>Elevate your drywall finishing process with the Platinum ECO Inside Corner Roller. Designed for professionals and DIY enthusiasts alike, this tool streamlines the embedding of corner tape, ensuring a crisp, professional finish every time. By combining lightweight construction with high-performance materials, this roller minimizes fatigue while maximizing the quality of your interior wall transitions.</p><h2>Precision Engineering for Superior Results</h2><p>Forget the frustration of damaged corner beads or uneven tape application. The ECO Inside Corner Roller features specialized nylon rollers that glide effortlessly over your work, providing consistent pressure without marring the surface. Its intuitive design allows for rapid, uniform results, significantly reducing the time spent on manual smoothing and touch-ups.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Non-Marring Nylon Rollers:</strong> Engineered to apply firm, even pressure to corner tape while protecting delicate corner beads from scratches or indentations.</li><li><strong>Universal Compatibility:</strong> Features a standard threaded connection that fits most common painter’s poles and broom handles, allowing you to reach high corners without a ladder.</li><li><strong>Ergonomic Efficiency:</strong> Lightweight and balanced, this tool is built to reduce wrist and arm strain during extended finishing projects.</li><li><strong>Durable Construction:</strong> Built to withstand the rigors of daily job site use, ensuring long-term reliability for your drywall toolkit.</li><li><strong>Seamless Integration:</strong> Designed to work harmoniously with standard drywall finishing workflows, making it an essential addition for any professional contractor.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-CRE | | Tool Type | Inside Corner Roller | | Material | Nylon Rollers | | Compatibility | Standard Coarse Thread Poles | | Price | $59.00 | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools |</p>",The Platinum ECO Inside Corner Roller features nylon rollers for smooth corner finishing. Attaches to any standard coarse thread painter's pole or broom handle.,59.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-CRE_4e69c1aa.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-cre",1428,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-EXT3IN1-1,,Extendable Angle Head Handle,simple,"<h2>Elevate Your Drywall Finishing Precision</h2><p>Achieve flawless corners and reach challenging heights with the Platinum Extendable Angle Head Handle. Engineered for professional drywall contractors who demand both versatility and durability, this tool eliminates the need for cumbersome ladders or scaffolding. Its robust yet lightweight design ensures you maintain total control during extended use, reducing fatigue while maximizing your daily output.</p><h2>Built for the Demanding Job Site</h2><p>Crafted from premium-grade aluminum, this handle offers the perfect balance of structural integrity and portability. The telescoping mechanism operates smoothly, allowing for rapid adjustments between 45 and 70 inches to accommodate varying ceiling heights and tight corner configurations. Outfitted with ergonomic grips, it provides a secure, comfortable hold that minimizes hand strain, even during high-volume finishing tasks.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Telescoping Versatility:</strong> Effortlessly adjusts from 45 to 70 inches, providing the reach necessary for high walls and vaulted ceilings.</li><li><strong>Lightweight Aluminum Construction:</strong> High-grade materials ensure a durable, corrosion-resistant build that remains easy to maneuver throughout the workday.</li><li><strong>Ergonomic Handling:</strong> Designed with comfortable, non-slip grips to enhance control and reduce operator fatigue.</li><li><strong>Professional-Grade Reliability:</strong> Engineered to withstand the rigors of daily job site use, ensuring consistent performance for long-term projects.</li><li><strong>Seamless Integration:</strong> Compatible with standard angle heads, making it an essential addition to any professional drywall finishing kit.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-EXT3IN1-1 | | Product Type | Extendable Angle Head Handle | | Material | High-grade Aluminum | | Adjustable Length | 45"" - 70"" | | Price | $75.00 |</p>","Platinum Extendable Angle Head Handle adjusts from 45–70"" for reaching high work and tight spaces. High-grade lightweight aluminum with comfortable grips.",75.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-EXT3IN1-1_dff530ee.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-ext3in1-1",1429,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-EBH,,"Extendable Flat Box Handle 40"" – 64""",simple,"<h2>Elevate Your Drywall Finishing Precision</h2><p>Experience the perfect balance of durability and maneuverability with the Platinum Extendable Flat Box Handle. Engineered specifically for the rigorous demands of professional drywall contractors, this tool is designed to streamline your workflow while ensuring a flawless, professional-grade finish on every seam. By combining high-strength materials with an intuitive, adjustable design, this handle empowers you to tackle high-reach applications with confidence and ease.</p><h2>Built for the Professional Contractor</h2><p>Constructed from premium-grade anodized aluminum, this handle offers an exceptional strength-to-weight ratio, effectively reducing operator fatigue during long shifts. The telescopic design provides seamless length adjustment from 40 to 64 inches, allowing you to transition effortlessly between standard wall heights and elevated ceiling work. A robust, integrated locking mechanism guarantees rock-solid stability at any setting, preventing slippage and ensuring the consistent pressure required for a smooth, uniform compound application.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Precision Engineering:</strong> Crafted from lightweight, corrosion-resistant anodized aluminum for long-term durability in harsh job-site environments.</li><li><strong>Versatile Reach:</strong> Telescopic adjustment range of 40"" to 64"" provides the flexibility needed for diverse wall and ceiling configurations.</li><li><strong>Secure Locking System:</strong> Features a reliable, high-tension locking mechanism that maintains your chosen length securely throughout the finishing process.</li><li><strong>Ergonomic Control:</strong> Designed to provide superior leverage and tactile feedback, allowing for precise control of your flat box for a professional, streak-free finish.</li><li><strong>Professional Compatibility:</strong> Optimized for seamless integration with standard flat boxes, making it an essential upgrade for any drywall finishing kit.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-EBH | | Product Type | Extendable Flat Box Handle | | Material | Anodized Aluminum | | Adjustable Length | 40"" – 64"" | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Price | $169.00 |</p>","The Platinum Extendable Flat Box Handle adjusts from 40"" to 64"" with a secure locking mechanism. Lightweight anodized aluminum for smooth, consistent finishes.",169.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-EBH_de691736.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-ebh",1430,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-ICA,,Inside 90 Degree Applicator,simple,"<h2>Achieve Flawless Interior Corners with Precision</h2><p>Elevate your drywall finishing workflow with the Platinum Inside 90 Degree Applicator. Engineered for professionals who demand consistency and speed, this applicator head streamlines the process of applying joint compound to interior corners. By ensuring an even, uniform distribution of material, it significantly reduces the need for extensive sanding and touch-ups, allowing you to move through your projects with greater efficiency and confidence.</p><h2>Built for the Demanding Job Site</h2><p>Durability is at the core of the Platinum design philosophy. This applicator head is constructed from high-grade materials capable of withstanding the rigors of daily professional use. Whether you are tackling a residential renovation or a large-scale commercial build, this tool provides the reliable performance required to maintain a high standard of finish across every corner of the room.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Precision Engineering:</strong> Specifically calibrated for 90-degree interior corners to ensure a perfect fit and consistent compound thickness.</li><li><strong>Professional Finish:</strong> Delivers a smooth, professional-grade application that minimizes waste and maximizes productivity.</li><li><strong>Robust Construction:</strong> Crafted for longevity, ensuring the tool maintains its shape and performance over extended periods of heavy-duty use.</li><li><strong>Seamless Integration:</strong> Designed to work effortlessly with standard drywall finishing equipment for a streamlined, intuitive user experience.</li><li><strong>Time-Saving Efficiency:</strong> Significantly accelerates the taping and finishing process, allowing for faster project completion without sacrificing quality.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-ICA | | Product Type | Inside 90 Degree Applicator | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Price | $59.00 |</p>","The Platinum Inside 90 Degree Applicator Head applies joint compound effortlessly on interior corners. Precision-crafted for smooth, professional-grade finishes.",59.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-ICA_3f4f7b92.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-ica",1431,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-CR,,Inside Corner Roller,simple,"<h2>Achieve Flawless 90-Degree Corners with Precision</h2><p>The Platinum Inside Corner Roller is an essential instrument for professional drywall finishers who demand perfection in every seam. Engineered to streamline the taping process, this tool ensures that paper tape is seated firmly and uniformly into inside corners, eliminating air pockets and excess compound for a professional-grade finish that stands the test of time.</p><h2>Superior Bedding Performance</h2><p>Designed for efficiency and consistency, this roller allows you to quickly transition from applying joint compound to securing the tape. By applying consistent pressure along the 90-degree angle, the tool effectively forces out trapped air and surplus mud, creating a tight, reliable bond between the tape and the substrate. This critical step sets the stage for a clean, sharp corner that requires minimal sanding and finishing work.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Precision Engineering:</strong> Specifically calibrated for 90-degree inside corners to ensure perfect tape alignment every time.</li><li><strong>Optimized Bonding:</strong> Forces excess joint compound from beneath the tape, ensuring a secure, bubble-free adhesion.</li><li><strong>Workflow Efficiency:</strong> Designed to be used immediately after tape application, significantly reducing the time spent on manual corner finishing.</li><li><strong>Professional Results:</strong> Creates a crisp, sharp corner profile that serves as the ideal foundation for subsequent finishing steps.</li><li><strong>System Compatibility:</strong> Pairs perfectly with corner flushers or angle heads to efficiently remove remaining compound and finalize the corner geometry.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-CR | | Product Type | Inside Corner Roller | | Application | Drywall Taping and Finishing | | Corner Angle | 90 Degrees | | Price | $79.99 |</p>","The Platinum Inside Corner Roller embeds paper tape into inside 90-degree corners. Roll over tape to force out excess compound and create a sharp, clean corner.",79.99,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-CR_e8bbf114.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-cr",1432,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-MNBH,,Mini Box Handle,simple,"<h2>Precision Maneuverability for Tight Spaces</h2><p>Take control of your drywall finishing in confined areas with the Platinum Mini Flat Box Handle. Engineered specifically for professionals who encounter cramped closets, small bathrooms, and narrow hallways, this compact tool ensures you never have to sacrifice a professional finish due to space constraints. By reducing the overall length of your flat box setup, you gain the agility needed to navigate tight corners and restricted work zones with ease and confidence.</p><h2>Built for the Demanding Job Site</h2><p>Durability meets lightweight design in this essential finishing accessory. Crafted from premium-grade anodized aluminum, the Platinum Mini Handle is built to withstand the rigors of daily construction environments while resisting corrosion and wear. Its robust construction provides a solid, reliable connection to your flat box, ensuring consistent pressure and smooth operation throughout your workday.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Compact 13-Inch Design:</strong> Specifically engineered to provide maximum reach in the smallest of spaces where standard handles are too cumbersome.</li><li><strong>Premium Anodized Aluminum:</strong> Offers a superior strength-to-weight ratio, ensuring the tool remains lightweight for reduced fatigue while maintaining long-term durability.</li><li><strong>Professional-Grade Reliability:</strong> Designed to meet the high standards of drywall contractors, providing a secure and stable grip for precise mud application.</li><li><strong>Enhanced Versatility:</strong> Easily integrates with your existing flat box system, allowing you to switch between standard and mini handles depending on the project requirements.</li><li><strong>Corrosion Resistant:</strong> The high-quality finish protects the handle from moisture and drywall compound buildup, simplifying cleanup and extending service life.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-MNBH | | Product Type | Mini Flat Box Handle | | Material | Anodized Aluminum | | Length | 13 inches | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools |</p>","The Platinum Mini Box Handle (13"") allows use of flat boxes in tight spaces and small closets. High-quality anodized aluminum for long service life.",62.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-MNBH_263be1c5.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-mnbh",1433,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-OCA,,Outside 90 Degree Applicator,simple,"<h2>Precision Finishing for Outside Corners</h2><p>Achieve professional-grade results on every outside 90-degree angle with the Platinum Outside 90 Degree Applicator. Engineered for high-volume efficiency, this tool streamlines the process of applying joint compound, ensuring a consistent, uniform ribbon of mud on both sides of your corner bead simultaneously. Whether you are a seasoned contractor or a dedicated professional, this applicator is designed to significantly reduce your finishing time while maintaining impeccable quality.</p><h2>Engineered for Versatility and Speed</h2><p>Stop wasting time with manual application methods. The Platinum Outside 90 Degree Applicator is built to integrate seamlessly into your existing drywall finishing workflow. Its universal design ensures compatibility with all standard compound tubes and corner boxes, making it an essential addition to your tool kit. By automating the mudding process for corner beads, you can achieve a cleaner, faster, and more reliable finish on every project.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Universal Compatibility:</strong> Designed to attach effortlessly to all major brands of compound tubes and corner boxes for maximum versatility.</li><li><strong>Dual-Sided Application:</strong> Simultaneously dispenses precise ribbons of joint compound to both sides of 90-degree outside corners.</li><li><strong>Enhanced Efficiency:</strong> Dramatically accelerates the installation of mud-set corner beads, saving valuable labor hours on the job site.</li><li><strong>Professional Consistency:</strong> Delivers a uniform amount of compound, reducing the need for excessive cleanup or secondary passes.</li><li><strong>Durable Construction:</strong> Built to withstand the rigors of daily professional use in demanding drywall environments.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-OCA | | Product Type | Outside 90 Degree Applicator | | Application | Drywall Corner Bead Finishing | | Compatibility | Universal (Fits standard compound tubes and corner boxes) | | Price | $59.00 |</p>",The Platinum Outside 90 Degree Applicator dispenses joint compound to both sides of outside 90-degree angles. Fits all major compound tube and corner box brands.,59.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-OCA_43eb46ed.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-oca",1434,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-OCR,,Outside 90 Degree Corner Roller,simple,"<h2>Achieve Flawless Corner Finishes with Precision</h2><p>Elevate your drywall finishing process with the Platinum Outside 90 Degree Corner Roller. Engineered for professionals who demand consistency and speed, this specialized tool is essential for securing paper-faced corner bead. By effectively eliminating excess joint compound from beneath the bead, it ensures a superior, bubble-free bond that stands the test of time.</p><h2>Engineered for Performance and Durability</h2><p>Designed to streamline your workflow, this roller features high-grade nylon wheels that glide effortlessly along the corner bead. The smooth rolling action prevents tearing or scuffing of the paper surface, allowing you to achieve a crisp, professional 90-degree angle with minimal effort. Whether you are tackling a large-scale commercial project or a residential renovation, this tool provides the reliability needed to produce high-quality, seamless results every time.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Precision Compounding:</strong> Expertly forces out trapped air and excess compound to create a rock-solid adhesion between the bead and the drywall.</li><li><strong>Smooth-Glide Technology:</strong> High-quality nylon rollers ensure fluid movement, reducing operator fatigue during extended use.</li><li><strong>Professional Finish:</strong> Specifically calibrated for 90-degree outside corners, ensuring perfectly sharp edges that are ready for final finishing.</li><li><strong>Essential for Paper-Faced Bead:</strong> A critical addition to any drywall finisher's toolkit when working with paper-faced corner bead systems.</li><li><strong>Robust Construction:</strong> Built to withstand the rigors of daily job site use while maintaining consistent performance.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-OCR | | Product Type | Outside 90 Degree Corner Roller | | Material | Nylon Rollers | | Application | Paper-faced corner bead installation | | Price | $69.99 |</p>","The Platinum Outside 90 Degree Corner Roller squeezes excess compound from paper-faced corner bead. Nylon rollers for a strong, smooth bond.",69.99,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-OCR_9ef2eaec.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-ocr",1435,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-3.5CF,,Platinum 3.5 Corner Flusher,simple,"<h2>Precision Finishing for Every Corner</h2><p>Achieve professional-grade results with the Platinum 3.5 Corner Flusher, an essential tool for drywall contractors who demand consistency and speed. Engineered to streamline the finishing process, this flusher ensures that your internal corner joints are perfectly feathered and smooth, eliminating the need for tedious manual sanding and touch-ups. Whether you are working on residential renovations or large-scale commercial projects, this tool provides the reliability required to maintain a high-quality finish across every wall.</p><h2>Built for Efficiency</h2><p>Designed to integrate seamlessly with your existing drywall finishing setup, the Platinum 3.5 Corner Flusher is crafted to handle the rigors of daily job-site use. Its robust construction ensures longevity, while the precision-engineered blade geometry allows for optimal compound distribution. By automating the corner finishing process, you can significantly reduce labor time while achieving a level of uniformity that is difficult to replicate by hand.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Professional-Grade Performance:</strong> Engineered for consistent, high-quality results in internal corner applications.</li><li><strong>Time-Saving Design:</strong> Dramatically reduces the time spent on manual finishing and sanding.</li><li><strong>Durable Construction:</strong> Built with premium materials to withstand the demanding environment of professional drywall installation.</li><li><strong>Seamless Integration:</strong> Compatible with standard drywall finishing handles and equipment for immediate use.</li><li><strong>Precision Feathering:</strong> Ensures smooth, clean edges that are ready for painting or texturing with minimal effort.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-3.5CF | | Product Type | Corner Flusher | | Size | 3.5 inches | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Price | $80.00 |</p>","Platinum 3.5"" Corner Flusher in surgical stainless spring steel. Fits all major brands of angle head or flusher handles.",80.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-3.5CF_d0f6ed93.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-3.5cf",1436,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-FIN,,Platinum Drywall Starter Finishing Set,simple,"<h2>Professional-Grade Precision for Every Seam</h2><p>Elevate your drywall finishing workflow with the Platinum Drywall Starter Finishing Set. Engineered for contractors who demand consistency and efficiency, this comprehensive kit provides the essential tools required to achieve flawless, professional-grade joints with minimal effort. Whether you are tackling a renovation or a large-scale commercial build, these tools are designed to streamline your taping and finishing process, ensuring a smooth, paint-ready surface every time.</p><h2>Built for the Job Site</h2><p>Constructed with durability and ergonomics in mind, the Platinum finishing suite minimizes operator fatigue while maximizing output. Each component is calibrated to handle the rigors of daily professional use, offering the reliability needed to meet tight deadlines without compromising on quality. This set serves as the perfect foundation for any drywall professional looking to upgrade their toolkit with high-performance, long-lasting equipment.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Professional Efficiency:</strong> Designed to significantly reduce finishing time compared to manual hand-tooling methods.</li><li><strong>Ergonomic Design:</strong> Balanced construction reduces wrist and arm strain during extended periods of use.</li><li><strong>High-Quality Materials:</strong> Built from premium, corrosion-resistant components for long-term durability on the job site.</li><li><strong>Seamless Integration:</strong> Perfectly suited for both novice finishers looking to upgrade and seasoned pros needing a reliable secondary set.</li><li><strong>Precision Control:</strong> Engineered for consistent mud application and smooth feathering across all drywall joints.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-FIN | | Product Type | Drywall Finishing Set | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools | | Price | $1,399.00 |</p>",Platinum Drywall Starter Finishing Set — a complete professional kit of essential drywall taping and finishing tools.,1399.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-FIN_a78d7a56.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-fin",1437,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
Platinum,PT-TP,,Semi Automatic Drywall Taper,simple,"<h2>Accelerate Your Drywall Workflow</h2><p>Upgrade your finishing efficiency with the Platinum Semi-Automatic Drywall Taper. Designed to bridge the gap between manual hand-taping and heavy-duty automatic tools, this device is an essential asset for contractors looking to reduce labor time without the steep investment of high-end mechanical systems. Whether you are a seasoned professional aiming for consistent output or a DIY enthusiast tackling a large-scale renovation, this tool ensures a uniform application of compound, significantly streamlining your taping process.</p><h2>Precision Mud Application</h2><p>Achieving a professional finish requires consistency, and the Platinum Taper delivers exactly that. By integrating directly with a standard 5-gallon bucket of thinned joint compound, the tool coats your tape as you pull, eliminating the need for messy, manual pre-loading. The integrated adjustment wing nut allows you to dial in the precise thickness of the mud application, giving you full control over your finish and minimizing waste on the job site.</p><h2>Key Features</h2><ul><li><strong>Enhanced Efficiency:</strong> Dramatically reduces the time spent on taping seams compared to traditional hand-application methods.</li><li><strong>Adjustable Flow Control:</strong> Features a precision wing nut that allows users to customize the mud-to-tape ratio for optimal coverage.</li><li><strong>Seamless Integration:</strong> Designed to work effortlessly with standard 5-gallon buckets, making it easy to set up and clean.</li><li><strong>User-Friendly Design:</strong> Intuitive operation makes it accessible for first-time users while maintaining the durability required for daily professional use.</li><li><strong>Consistent Results:</strong> Ensures an even, reliable layer of compound on every pull, reducing the need for touch-ups and sanding.</li></ul><h2>Technical Specifications</h2><p>| Specification | Detail | | :--- | :--- | | Brand | Platinum | | SKU | PT-TP | | Product Type | Semi-Automatic Drywall Taper | | Compatibility | Standard 5-Gallon Buckets | | Adjustment Mechanism | Wing Nut Flow Control | | Category | Drywall Finishing Tools |</p>","The Platinum Semi-Automatic Drywall Taper applies mud to tape as you pull, speeding up the taping process for professionals and first-time tapers alike.",145.00,,https://drywalltoolbox.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Platinum/Products/PT-TP_58c290ca.webp,Drywall Finishing Tools > Platinum > Tools,"Platinum, pt-tp",1438,1,0,visible,,,taxable,,1,,,,0,,,,,1,,,,,,,,,,,Brand,Platinum,1,1
